 107:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 108:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** /** @defgroup RCC_Exported_Functions_Group1 Initialization and de-initialization functions
 109:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *  @brief    Initialization and Configuration functions
 110:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****   *
 111:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****   @verbatim
 112:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****   ===============================================================================
 113:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****            ##### Initialization and de-initialization functions #####
 114:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****   ===============================================================================
 115:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..]
 116:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       This section provides functions allowing to configure the internal/external oscillators
 117:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (MSI, HSE, HSI, LSE, LSI, PLL, CSS and MCO) and the System buses clocks (SYSCLK, AHB, APB1
 118:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       and APB2).
 119:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 120:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..] Internal/external clock and PLL configuration
 121:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) MSI (Multispeed internal), Seven frequency ranges are available: 65.536 kHz,
 122:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           131.072 kHz, 262.144 kHz, 524.288 kHz, 1.048 MHz, 2.097 MHz (default value) and 4.194 MHz
 123:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 124:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) HSI (high-speed internal), 16 MHz factory-trimmed RC used directly or through
 125:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           the PLL as System clock source.
 126:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) LSI (low-speed internal), ~37 KHz low consumption RC used as IWDG and/or RTC
 127:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           clock source.
 128:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 129:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) HSE (high-speed external), 1 to 24 MHz crystal oscillator used directly or
 130:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           through the PLL as System clock source. Can be used also as RTC clock source.
 131:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 132:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) LSE (low-speed external), 32 KHz oscillator used as RTC clock source.
 133:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 134:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) PLL (clocked by HSI or HSE), featuring different output clocks:
 135:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****         (++) The first output is used to generate the high speed system clock (up to 32 MHz)
 136:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****         (++) The second output is used to generate the clock for the USB OTG FS (48 MHz)
 137:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 138:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) CSS (Clock security system), once enable using the macro __HAL_RCC_CSS_ENABLE()
 139:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           and if a HSE clock failure occurs(HSE used directly or through PLL as System
 140:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           clock source), the System clocks automatically switched to MSI and an interrupt
 141:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           is generated if enabled. The interrupt is linked to the Cortex-M0+ NMI
 142:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           (Non-Maskable Interrupt) exception vector.
 143:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 144:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) MCO1/MCO2/MCO3 (microcontroller clock output), used to output SYSCLK, HSI, LSI, MSI, LSE,
 145:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           HSE, HSI48 or PLL clock (through a configurable prescaler) on PA8/PA9/PB13 pins.
 146:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Tilen\AppData\Local\Temp\ccC0CAdr.s 			page 4


 147:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****     [..] System, AHB and APB buses clocks configuration
 148:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) Several clock sources can be used to drive the System clock (SYSCLK): MSI, HSI,
 149:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           HSE and PLL.
 150:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           The AHB clock (HCLK) is derived from System clock through configurable
 151:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           prescaler and used to clock the CPU, memory and peripherals mapped
 152:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           on AHB bus (DMA, GPIO...). APB1 (PCLK1) and APB2 (PCLK2) clocks are derived
 153:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           from AHB clock through configurable prescalers and used to clock
 154:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           the peripherals mapped on these buses. You can use
 155:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           "HAL_RCC_GetSysClockFreq()" function to retrieve the frequencies of these clocks.
 156:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 157:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       -@- All the peripheral clocks are derived from the System clock (SYSCLK) except:
 158:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           (+@) RTC: RTC clock can be derived either from the LSI, LSE or HSE clock
 159:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****               divided by 2 to 16. You have to use __HAL_RCC_RTC_CONFIG() and __HAL_RCC_RTC_ENABLE()
 160:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****               macros to configure this clock.
 161:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           (+@) LCD: LCD clock can be derived either from the LSI, LSE or HSE clock
 162:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****               divided by 2 to 16. You have to use __HAL_RCC_LCD_CONFIG()
 163:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****               macros to configure this clock.
 164:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           (+@) USB FS and RNG: USB FS require a frequency equal to 48 MHz to work correctly.
 165:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****                This clock is derived of the main PLL through PLL Multiplier or HSI48 RC oscillator.
 166:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 167:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           (+@) IWDG clock which is always the LSI clock.
 168:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c **** 
 169:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****       (#) The maximum frequency of the SYSCLK and HCLK is 32 MHz, PCLK2 32 MHz
 170:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           and PCLK1 32 MHz. Depending on the device voltage range, the maximum
 171:Drivers/STM32L0xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32l0xx_hal_rcc.c ****           frequency should be adapted accordingly.
